e,"sense_count":26},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11381","n11386","n11387","n11388","n11389","n11390","n11407"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to create, to make","examples":[{"text":"يَـٰٓأَيُّهَا ٱلنَّاسُ ٱعْبُدُوا۟ رَبَّكُمُ ٱلَّذِى خَلَقَكُمْ وَٱلَّذِينَ مِن قَبْلِكُمْ لَعَلَّكُمْ تَتَّقُونَ","english":"O mankind, worship your Lord, who created you and those before you, that you may become righteous -"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shape, to form"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be suitable, be fit"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to perfume"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of خَلَقَ (ḵalaqa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"creation","examples":[{"text":"لِخَلْقِ بِيئَةٍ جَيِّدَةٍ، يَجِبُ أَنّ تُهَوِّيَ حَوْضَ السَّمَكِ بِٱنْتِظَامٍ.","english":"To create a good environment, you must aerate the fish tank regularly."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"creation (“all which exists”), creatures","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"people","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"أَنَامُ مِلْءَ جُفُونِي عَنْ شَوارِدِهَا / وَيَسْهَرُ الْخَلْقُ جَرَّاهَا وَيَخْتَصِمُ","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pleb, plebeian"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"natural disposition, character, nature"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inborn quality"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"manners, character"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"morals, morality","examples":[{"text":"Ahmad Shawqi\nوَإِنَّمَا ٱلْأُمَمُ ٱلْأَخْلَاقُ مَا بَقِيَتْ / فَإِنْ هُمُ ذَهَبَتْ أَخْلَاقُهُمْ ذَهَبُوا\nwaʔinnamā l-ʔumamu l-ʔaḵlāqu mā baqiyat / faʔin humu ḏahabat ʔaḵlāquhum ḏahabū","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"anger, irritation","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bravery","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"religion","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"humanity","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"refinement","tags":["Arabic","Modern","Standard"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of خِلْقَة (ḵilqa)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be old and worn out (of a garment)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be smooth and soft (of an item, through wear)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of خَلِقَ (ḵaliqa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rags"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"old age"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"men, people"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"worn, threadbare"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Inherited from Proto-Semitic *ḫalaq-, cognate with Biblical Hebrew חָלַק (ḥɔláq, ḥālaq, “to divide”), Classical Syriac ܚܠܩ (ḥəlaq, “to divide, apportion”), Sabaean [script needed] (ḫlq, “compensation, portion, lot”), and Minaean [script needed] (ḫlq). Took on the senses of creation and formation prior to the advent of Islam, as indicated by passages like Qur'an (in Arabic), 609–632 CE, 39:38, where the term is already understood by non-Muslim interlocutors, likely influenced by ancient Near Eastern mythology, in which the world was created by dividing pre-existing matter.\n\nProbably denominal from the perfume compound خَلُوق (ḵalūq), خِلَاق (ḵilāq), which is then from the base stem “to create, to compose” above.\n\nPlausibly a liquid variant of خ ر ق (ḵ r q), but it is sensible that it rather relates to Biblical Hebrew חָלַק (ḥɔláq, “to be smooth, slippery”) and Akkadian 𒄩𒀀 (ḫalāqum, “to vanish”)."},"ipa":["/xa.la.qa/","/xa.lu.qa/","/xal.la.qa/","/xalq/","/xu.luq/","/xi.laq/","/xa.li.qa/","/xa.laq/"]}